issue.title: Deprecate example MockitoExtension in favor of official extension from Mockito
issue.body:
## Overview

Since the Mockito team has released official support for JUnit Jupiter, we should deprecate and eventually remove the example `MockitoExtension` in this repository.

## Related Issues

- https://github.com/junit-team/junit5/issues/1344

## Deliverables

- [x] Deprecate the example `MockitoExtension` within the `junit5-samples` repository.
- [x] Consider completely deleting it -- if not now, then at a later date (potentially addressed in a separate GitHub issue)

body: @sbrannen I can't edit the description but there should probably be a second task such as "Update the user guide code sample to eliminate ``@Mock`` parameter resolution" given https://github.com/mockito/mockito/issues/1348 is outstanding.  It's also worth noting that the matching by type and name in the current code snippet may never be supported.
@smoyer64 Good point! I think we might need to find a different example for parameter resolution.
I expounded on the deliverable. ðŸ˜‰
